1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 20]

23
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,690
Hello. China Customs.

24
00:01:37,710 --> 00:01:38,330
This way, please.

25
00:01:39,230 --> 00:01:39,740
Thank you.

26
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:42,570
Attention, all units.

27
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,210
Liu Yang just passed
the diversion checkpoint.

28
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:08,780
Hello, this way.

29
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:16,170
Ma'am, China Customs.

30
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,730
We need to inspect your luggage.

31
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:18,780
Sure.

32
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,500
Bringing two empty suitcases back?

33
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:48,780
Isn't that allowed?

34
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,660
I run a Chinese restaurant in Seoul.

35
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,690
Some restaurant supplies

36
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:54,980
I have to carry over.

37
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:57,260
They were inspected on departure.

38
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,890
Got a problem?

39
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,010
No problem.

40
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,540
Can I go now?

41
00:03:01,910 --> 00:03:02,850
Thanks for cooperating.

42
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,010
Thanks.

43
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,690
Sure it's him?

44
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,410
Yes.

45
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,010
I went myself to make sure

46
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:23,100
they got it right.

47
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:25,380
Looks like he's loyal.

48
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:26,730
What do you mean?

49
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,820
You don't know?

50
00:03:28,190 --> 00:03:29,060
That beach

51
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:31,410
is where Sa Ziyi
was found after suicide.

52
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:35,060
If that's true,

53
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,380
he's someone we can trust.

54
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,610
Has he been going there often?

55
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,780
Every other day.

56
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,820
He should be there today.

57
00:03:43,710 --> 00:03:44,890
So he's waiting for someone.

58
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,450
Hope we find him first.

59
00:04:13,910 --> 00:04:15,570
Why'd you pick a place like this?

60
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,410
It's safe.

61
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:20,290
I figured

62
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:22,140
you wouldn't want anyone overhearing.

63
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,700
Go ahead.

64
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,660
What do you know?

65
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:42,050
A few days ago, I got a call.

66
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:44,850
Someone calling himself Mr. E.

67
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:45,730
Mr. E?

68
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,290
He wanted to work with me.

69
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:50,660
He said he'd bring you down

70
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,660
and pass all your resources

71
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,850
to me.

72
00:04:55,310 --> 00:04:56,610
Sounds good.

73
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,540
You should work with him.

74
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,810
Why tell me?

75
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:01,850
I don't trust him.

76
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:04,140
If he can betray you today,

77
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,580
he can betray me tomorrow.

78
00:05:06,430 --> 00:05:07,930
So I asked you out

79
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:10,580
to help find him,

80
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,850
then we can work together.

81
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:18,220
Why should I trust you?

82
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:19,780
I have the recording.

83
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:26,540
I told you this

84
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,660
because I want to work with you.

85
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,140
Work together?

86
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:31,140
Why?

87
00:05:31,510 --> 00:05:32,850
I've been watching you.

88
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:35,020
Although you're new in the game,

89
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,780
and you haven't done much.

90
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,850
That's because the airport mule network

91
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:40,700
is controlled by Sa Ziyi.

92
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:42,900
I couldn't scale up even if I wanted to.

93
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,340
So?

94
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:48,220
Can you tell who it is?

95
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:52,980
How can I?

96
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:54,540
Voice is distorted.

97
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,020
Why are you helping me?

98
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:06,700
Because we're both women.

99
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,490
You're a year older,

100
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,100
I'll call you sis.

101
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:11,100
Sis,

102
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,140
I know exactly

103
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,250
how hard your path has been.

104
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:15,220
Because,

105
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,050
I've been through the same.

106
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:19,370
I asked you to help me before.

107
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,290
Why didn't you come?

108
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,370
Still because we're both women.

109
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:26,730
Why should you

110
00:06:26,830 --> 00:06:27,900
be Wu Zetian
[*powerful Chinese empress]

111
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,020
and I end up as Princess Taiping?
[*Wu Zetian's daughter]

112
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:35,490
Still want to be my equal.

113
00:06:36,390 --> 00:06:37,580
Why can't I?

114
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:39,490
Sisters working together,

115
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:41,410
better than those men, right?

116
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,460
You're right.

117
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,930
If you feel dizzy,

118
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:04,250
you can lean on me.

119
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:07,340
I'm fine.

120
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,610
Ziyi?

121
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:19,140
Ziyi?

122
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,460
Well, Ms. Du,

123
00:08:07,390 --> 00:08:08,810
you've got yourself a villa now.

124
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,460
Compared to Ms. Sa's place,
it's nothing.

125
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,730
Coffee or tea?

126
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:48,770
No need.

127
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:49,940
Just say it.

128
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:51,730
Alright.

129
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,060
Please sit.

130
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:00,610
I heard you've been looking for me

131
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:01,610
after you got out.

132
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,530
Just looking for Ziyi's killer.

133
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:10,220
So you think

134
00:09:10,670 --> 00:09:12,650
whoever took over Ms. Sa's turf

135
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,980
is the most likely killer, right?

136
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:16,530
What do you think?

137
00:09:16,910 --> 00:09:18,300
I'm right here.

138
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:19,580
I can tell you,

139
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:20,610
I'm not.

140
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,180
I admit it.

141
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,490
I took over Ms. Sa's turf

142
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:27,060
and her airport route.

143
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:30,180
But only after she died.

144
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:34,340
Back then she tried
to recruit me, I refused

145
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:36,530
and said some harsh things.

146
00:09:36,870 --> 00:09:38,370
I was young and reckless.

147
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:41,530
But that doesn't mean
I wanted to replace her.

148
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:43,980
As far as I know,

149
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,180
all our old resources

150
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:47,610
are now in your hands.

151
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:49,340
Yes.

152
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,370
That's because

153
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:53,100
a Mr. E reached out to me.

154
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:54,490
Mr. E?

155
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:55,490
Yes.

156
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:57,770
I call him Mr. E

157
00:09:57,910 --> 00:09:59,100
because I've never

158
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,490
met him in person.

159
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:03,490
You trust someone

160
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:04,890
you've never met?

161
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:07,890
Because he mentioned the 'Dolls'.

162
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,010
And,

163
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:12,980
he said he could bring Ms. Sa down

164
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:16,180
and hand me all her resources.

165
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:17,650
Turns out,

166
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:18,700
he did.

167
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:19,940
Look,

168
00:10:20,550 --> 00:10:21,850
he lifted me from the streets

169
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,010
to here.

170
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:24,490
So you mean

171
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,060
he killed Ziyi?

172
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:28,460
I should be grateful.

173
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:29,770
But I

174
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:31,370
hate lying.

175
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:33,300
I think there's a good chance

176
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:34,490
he killed

177
00:10:34,870 --> 00:10:36,010
Ms. Sa.

178
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:38,940
Then why come to me?

179
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,890
I want you to help me find him.

180
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:44,420
This man controls me like a shadow.

181
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:46,250
I need to know who he is.

182
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:47,610
Do I know him?

183
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,420
You should.

184
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:52,100
He only finds mules for us.

185
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,250
Mule hound?

186
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:55,130
As far as we know,

187
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:58,180
Ms. Sa had one back then.

188
00:10:58,870 --> 00:11:00,100
How much do you know

189
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,370
about it, Shuo?

190
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:02,850
I've never seen him.

191
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,850
Did Ms. Sa never mention anything?

192
00:11:07,630 --> 00:11:09,250
Mule hound?

193
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,340
Sounds ugly.

194
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:12,250
Yeah, it's him.

195
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,370
Extremely accurate with people.

196
00:11:15,030 --> 00:11:16,370
He found

197
00:11:16,390 --> 00:11:17,300
most of our mules.

198
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,530
Just dangle bait,

199
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:20,530
and they bite.

200
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,340
You've kept him well hidden,

201
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:24,770
even I didn't know.

202
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,340
That was our agreement.

203
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,890
The fewer people who know him,

204
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,700
the easier he operates.

205
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,010
She did.

206
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,460
Just fragments of talk.

207
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:38,300
Then Shuo,

208
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:39,650
think it over carefully.

209
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:41,180
Finding him

210
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:42,250
benefits

211
00:11:42,510 --> 00:11:43,220
both you

212
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,490
and me.

213
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:49,980
You want to work with me?

214
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:12,220
Bring the bag.

215
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,250
Wanna show you something.

216
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:15,530
What is it?

217
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,460
A snuff bottle?

218
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,060
Where'd you snag it?

219
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:25,420
Snag it?

220
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:27,130
That sounds bad!

221
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,250
Let me tell you,

222
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,650
I took it from that old guy.

223
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:35,820
He's got a lot of antiques.

224
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:56,420
Can you tell
if this came from your shop?

225
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:57,890
Let me take a look.

226
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,180
No.

227
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:06,980
I have similar ones,

228
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,220
but the material's different.

229
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:09,370
Please check again.

230
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,060
Have you seen it anywhere?

231
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:14,300
Some antique furniture makers

232
00:13:14,630 --> 00:13:15,980
might collect old items

233
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,460
from folk sources.

234
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:31,300
Attention, all units.

235
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:32,700
Liu Yang just passed
the diversion checkpoint.

236
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,130
Over.

237
00:13:33,390 --> 00:13:33,820
Copy.

238
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:48,340
Hello,

239
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:49,980
please comply with our check.

240
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,370
Another check?

241
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:53,010
Yes.

242
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,490
Don't you have

243
00:14:16,510 --> 00:14:18,300
anything better to do?

244
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,820
It's almost midnight,

245
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,490
let people go home, alright?

246
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:24,820
Hurry up, please,

247
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,770
I'm exhausted.

248
00:14:32,550 --> 00:14:34,130
Do you need to check this too?

249
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:36,340
Same as last time.

250
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:38,460
Yes, thank you for your cooperation.

251
00:14:39,910 --> 00:14:40,580
Okay.

252
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:43,940
Hello.

253
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:45,420
This way please.

254
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,730
Any issues found?

255
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,060
Can I go now?

256
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:55,730
No issues.

257
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:56,700
Thank you.

258
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:18,340
Swap with me, I'll find Mr. Guo.

259
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:19,220
Okay.

260
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,130
Something's off.

261
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,180
Mr. Guo.

262
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:27,460
What's up?

263
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:28,370
Liu Yang just passed,

264
00:15:28,390 --> 00:15:29,220
but something's off.

265
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,130
Go on.

266
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:32,220
There's wet soil in her suitcase.

267
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,530
I checked Seoul's weather

268
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:34,820
in the briefing today,

269
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:35,980
heavy snow there.

270
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,250
I felt it carefully just now.

271
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,060
The marks look like

272
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:42,010
wheel tracks.

273
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:44,890
So I suspect before boarding,

274
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:47,220
there was another suitcase inside hers.

275
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,010
Are you sure?

276
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,940
Just a guess, no proof.

277
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,180
So I let her pass.

278
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:56,010
Whether international
or domestic arrival,

279
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:58,700
the cargo sorting
back corridor is connected.

280
00:15:59,670 --> 00:16:00,700
So it means

281
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:03,370
if someone tampers there,

282
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:05,980
international luggage could
be switched to domestic, right?

283
00:16:06,390 --> 00:16:07,730
That's a major find.

284
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:08,730
Stay here and keep watch.

285
00:16:08,910 --> 00:16:09,890
I'll report up.

286
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:10,420
Yes.

287
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:35,940
Sir,

288
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:37,370
is your boss in?

289
00:16:37,750 --> 00:16:38,530
Inside, yeah.

290
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:39,340
Good, thanks.

291
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,130
Who took this photo?

292
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:49,850
A photographer friend.

293
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:53,850
Sir!

294
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,250
Hello.

295
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:01,100
